.SH "NAME"
scnprintf \- Format a string and place it in a buffer
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ scnprintf('u
.BI "int scnprintf(char\ *\ " "buf" ", size_t\ " "size" ", const\ char\ *\ " "fmt" ", " "\&.\&.\&." ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIbuf\fR
.RS 4
The buffer to place the result into
.RE
.PP
\fIsize\fR
.RS 4
The size of the buffer, including the trailing null space
.RE
.PP
\fIfmt\fR
.RS 4
The format string to use
.RE
.PP
\fI\&.\&.\&.\fR
.RS 4
Arguments for the format string
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The return value is the number of characters written into
\fIbuf\fR
not including the trailing \*(Aq\e0\*(Aq\&. If
\fIsize\fR
is == 0 the function returns 0\&.
